From Gordon Sasamori Subject Re viewing postscript files under X windows In George Snyder writes In article Kin Cho writes I wonder if anybody know of a X window based postscript file viewer that runs under SunOS prefered HPUX or IBM If you are running Sun OpenWindows you can use pageview This is an X Window PostScript previewer like ghostview but displays much nicer Yes but it's broken on OW It does not handle multiple pages If you don't have the proper PostScript commands it will draw the entire document on the same page instead of pausing after each I haven't tried OW yet Gordon Sasamori CSIC MCU Design email Nippon Motorola voice FAX